document_notes.text:
This update for cloud-init fixes the following issues:

- Default route is not configured (bsc#1212879)
- cloud-final service failing in powerVS (bsc#1210273)
- Randomly generated passwords logged in clear-text to world-readable file (bsc#1184758, CVE-2021-3429)

notes.text: When instructing cloud-init to set a random password for a new user account, versions before 21.2 would write that password to the world-readable log file /var/log/cloud-init-output.log. This could allow a local user to log in as another user.

notes.text: Sensitive data could be exposed in logs of cloud-init before version 23.1.2. An attacker could use this information to find hashed passwords and possibly escalate their privilege.
